# Cloudflare Pages headers.
#
# Admin must ALWAYS revalidate. By default CF Pages sends no Cache-Control on
# HTML documents, so browsers — especially the WhatsApp/Instagram in-app
# webviews owners use — heuristically cache a stale admin.html for hours. After
# a redeploy the owner then sees an old admin (missing newly-added sections like
# Clients / Sell in store) until that heuristic cache expires. `no-cache` forces
# a revalidation on every load (304 when unchanged, fresh when redeployed), so
# admin changes show up immediately. Versioned assets (admin.js?v=, styles.css?v=)
# keep their long cache — only the HTML entry points need this.
/admin
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
/admin.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
